{"id":"242104226_Ergodicity_transitivity_and_regularity_for_linear_cellular_automata_over_Z","abstract":"We study the dynamical behavior of D-dimensional linear cellular automata over Zm. We provide an easy-to-check necessary and sufficient condition for a D-dimensional linear cellular automata over Zm to be ergodic and topologically transitive. As a byproduct, we get that for linear cellular automata ergodicity is equivalent to topological transitivity. Finally, we prove that for 1-dimensional linear cellular automata over Zm, regularity (denseness of periodic orbits) is equivalent to surjectivity.","authors":["Gianpiero Cattaneo","Enrico Formenti","Giovanni Manzini","Luciano Margara"],"meta":["February 2000Theoretical Computer Science 233(1-2):147-164","DOI:10.1016/S0304-3975(98)00005-X","SourceDBLP"],"references":["248202199_Yu_S_Undecidability_of_CA_Classification_Schemes_Complex_Systems_2_177-190","220995289_On_Ergodic_Linear_Cellular_Automata_over_Z","220452280_Periodic_Orbits_for_Additive_Cellular_Automata","268243749_Transitive_Cellular_Automata_are_Sensitive","265670591_An_Introduction_To_Chaotic_Dynamics_Systems","256555144_Rice's_theorem_for_the_limit_set_of_cellular_automataTheor_Comput_Sci1272229-254","242791764_Ergodicity_of_linear_cellular_automata_over_Z_m","231999510_Ergodic_aspects_of_cellular_automata","227031141_Exact_results_for_deterministic_cellular_automata","222938869_Dynamical_Characteristics_of_Linear_Cellular_Automata","222871688_Additive_one-dimensional_cellular_automata_are_chaotic_according_to_Devaney's_definition_of_chaos","222247830_Decision_Procedures_for_Surjectivity_and_Injectivity_of_Parallel_Maps_for_Tesselation_Structures","222245265_Linear_cellular_automata_over_Zm","220616859_On_the_Limit_Sets_of_Cellular_Automata","220544485_Endomorphisms_and_Automorphisms_of_the_Shift_Dynamical_Systems","220544152_On_the_Ergodic_Theory_of_Cellular_Automata","44505395_An_introduction_to_chaotic_dynamical_systems_Robert_L_Devaney","38330899_O